contents.name: GP Registration
contents.description: The registration of a Person to a certain General Practitioner. This can also be a registration to a GP practice, but generally a specific GP will be assigned from this practice.

contents.name: Healthcare Office
contents.description: Each care office has its own region as its working area. The care office controls the implementation of the Wlz in that region. An important task is the allocation of care. To this end, the care office makes contract agreements with care providers and ensures that a client with a valid indication decision receives appropriate care in an efficient manner (care delivery). The care office can agree with care providers on how they perform the care allocation, but remains responsible for this in all cases. The care office is the information hub in the region and ensures that the chain functions well. It monitors the throughput times of the message traffic and the quality of the information that the chain partners exchange.

contents.name: Municipality (Gemeente)
contents.description:
According to the WMO 2015, the municipality is responsible for supporting people who are not self-reliant on their own. The municipality ensures that citizens who apply for support are assessed and are directed to a Wmo provider that can provide the right support. 
 
According to the Youth Act, the municipality is responsible for all forms of youth assistance (including specialist assistance such as youth mental health care, youth support, closed youth assistance, and the 'prevention' part of youth health care). The municipality is also responsible within the youth system for the implementation of child protection measures and juvenile rehabilitation.

contents.name: Healthcare Office Region
contents.description: Daniël: Each (healthcare office) region consists of a collection of municipalities. (The relation with provinces is quite messy. Some provinces consist of 1 region, but some of multiple regions. And then there are regions that cross province borders. See for example this map: regioatlas.nl/kaarten#_zorgkantoorregios )

contents.name: Healthcare Provider
contents.description: The care provider provides the care taking into account the care allocation received and contract agreements with the care liaison office. The care provider notifies the care office of the start of the care and its termination. The care provider also reports changes to the care delivery and changes to the delivery status to the care office. A special role is reserved for the file holder, the preferred provider of the client who has an indication for residence. The file holder maintains contact with the client and the care office and is responsible for arranging bridging care. The file holder is the link between the provider that provides the bridging care and the care office.
